Assignment: Physically Based Simulator

This is a physically based simulator that uses some Camera code from Clemson's computer science department.
When compiled and run, a cross-struted mesh will appear paused. Press p to begin the simulation of the soft body.

There is also code for planes, emitters, and pointlike particles.

To be implemented:
Rigid Bodies

Keyboard Commands:
m = Change material colors
l = Toggle to cull face solid color mode/lighting mode
b = Toggle to blend mode
g = Show Grid
p = pause/unpause
q = Quit Simulation
